  "doc_id": "3239",
  "text": "As [CITATION_1] notes, this evolution of African higher education has been pioneered by public universities in response to growing demand for higher education. In view of the limited higher education opportunities in the continent relative to the population, a pluralistic, well-managed public university, with multitasking capability to reach various groups seems to be the most logical response to growing local and global demand for highly skilled labor.",
